## Assessment against brief + richness 10
Plan delivers exactly what the user asked for: a REAL WordPress site on the Surface (Docker, port 8090, bridged) + work-sample entry + integrated SEO analyzer with open signup. SEO-first focus is genuine, not cosmetic: content silos, 12 city LPs (9 TX + 3 NM) built on the competitor gap (Amarillo rivals have zero town-level LPs), LocalBusiness/Service/FAQ/Breadcrumb schema, Yoast sitemap/robots, CWV/caching, click-to-call conversion architecture, bilingual differentiator. 29 pages via scalable templates = production scope worthy of 10/10, not bespoke-page busywork. Design is bespoke and industry-fit (steel blue + safety orange, Barlow Condensed), derived from the client's actual minimal site and explicitly not the portfolio look. plan-eval passed all 5 rubric criteria; plan-gate confirmed prior gaps resolved. No contradictions, no unresolved architecture.

## Notes for demo-builder (non-blocking, do not re-run plan)
1. **workSamples.js `category`**: change `"Creative"` -> `"Utility"` (or `"Productivity"`). An SEO/local-business WordPress build is not Creative; eval/image steps shouldn't fail on this but fix it at build time.
2. **Analyzer integration must round-trip live**: `/free-seo-audit/` page must actually let the reviewer register (fake email/pw) and run an analysis on the deployed WP demo URL. deploy-test must exercise this exact flow, not just load the page. This is the user's explicit acceptance criterion.
3. **Playwright on Surface** is a prerequisite for `/seo/analyze` (JS rendering) — install chromium first if `playwright_available: false`, treat as setup not a mid-run surprise.
4. **Docker pull** must be via registered service (`run-server.ps1` owns startup), never blocked in `/run/exec` (Cloudflare 524). All runner scripts ASCII-only; no `?>` in any PHP; never touch the tunnel config.

No earlier step needs redoing. Plan is build-ready.

VERDICT: pass

